entry.title: H&M, Zara's Owner Stick With 'Made In Myanmar' After Coup, but Some Brands Exit
entry.content: Western retailers are increasingly divided over whether to buy clothes made in Myanmar, where some say laborÂ abuses have worsened under military rule.

entry.title: Ukraine Pushes South Into Strategic Kherson Region
entry.content: Ukrainian forces broke through Russian lines and made new advances in the southern Kherson region while expanding their rapid offensive in the east, retaking areas that Moscow now claims to be part of Russia.
